{
  "texts": [
    "Implementation of the technologies in operational missions requires further maturation through in-space demonstrations.\"",
    "The awarded companies are Eta Space of Meritt Island, Florida, Lockheed Martin of Littleton, Colorado, SpaceX of Hawthorne, California, and United Launch Alliance (ULA) of Centennial, Colorado.",
    "In the last two decades, several propulsion systems have been proposed and analysed for deep space exploration.",
    "The most promising ones are those fully based on nuclear thermal power (requiring liquid hydrogen) and on nuclear electric power plus cryogenic chemical propulsion for large velocity change maneuvers 3, 6, 7.",
    "The studies 6 and 7 show that large amounts of cryogenic fuels need to be stored in space and transferred between spacecraft."
  ]
}